findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges even after ownership renouncement, allowing them to lock/unlock, include/exclude from rewards and fees, change tax and liquidity fee, maximum transaction amount, marketingDivisor, minimum tokens for liquidity, buyBackUpperLimit, and marketing address. They can also enable/disable swap, liquify, and buyBack.
findings.function: Multiple functions (lock, unlock, includeInReward, excludeFromReward, etc.)

findings.title: DoS with block gas limit
findings.description: The contract may be vulnerable to denial of service attacks due to block gas limit.

findings.title: Out of gas
findings.description: The functions includeInReward() and _getCurrentSupply() may cause an OUT_OF_GAS exception if there is a long excluded addresses list.
